<L>__{interior greenhouse night.}
<A>__{fergus takes his place in the chair beside jody. jody begins to laugh under the hood. it turns into the sound of crying.}
<C>__{fergus}
<D>__{don't.}
<C>__{jody}
<D>__{i'm sorry.}
<A>__{the crying stops.}
<C>__{jody}
<D>__{help me.}
<C>__{fergus}
<D>__{how can i?}
<C>__{jody}
<D>__{i don't know. just help me. give me a cigarette.}
<A>__{fergus takes out a cigarette, lights it, and lifts up jody's hood so he can smoke.}
<C>__{jody}
<D>__{don't even smoke, you know that? it just seemed the right thing to do.}
<A>__{fergus watches him puff the cigarette, the hood just above his lips. jody coughs, but keeps the cigarette in his lips. fergus gently takes the cigarette from his mouth.}
<C>__{fergus}
<D>__{go to sleep now.}
<C>__{jody}
<D>__{i don't want to sleep. tell me something.}
<C>__{fergus}
<D>__{what?}
<C>__{jody}
<D>__{a story.}
<C>__{fergus}
<D>__{like the one about the frog?}
<C>__{jody}
<D>__{and the scorpion. no. tell me anything.}
<C>__{fergus}
<D>__{when i was a child...}
<C>__{jody}
<D>__{yeah?}
<C>__{fergus}
<D>__{i thought as a child. but when i became a man i put away childish things...}
<C>__{jody}
<D>__{what does that mean?}
<C>__{fergus}
<D>__{nothing.}
<C>__{jody}
<D>__{tell me something, anything.}
